{"name": "controller-companion", "metadata": {"name": "controller-companion", "version": "0.4.0", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["pillow", "pyautogui", "pygame", "pystray", "requests", "rich"], "summary": null, "upload_time": 1733860221}, "documentation": ["# Controller Companion\n\nEasily map controller shortcuts to an action.\nThe following actions are supported:\n- Kill a task by its name.\n- Execute a keyboard shortcut.\n- Execute an arbitrary console command.\n\n## Features\n- GUI and CLI options available\n- Supports a wide variety of controllers (those supported by [pygame](https://www.pygame.org))\n- Runs on Windows, Linux and Mac\n- Auto start on system boot (windows only for now)\n- GUI app can be compiled as a standalone executable (using [PyInstaller](https://pyinstaller.org)\n\n## How to run\n- CLI and GUI versions are accessible through [poetry](https://python-poetry.org/)\n- CLI:\n    - Multiple mappings can be created.\n    - One or multiple input controller key combination that triggers an action can be defined using --input. The keys of one individual input combination are separated by commas, while each distinct input combination is separated by a space. \n    - One or multiple actions can be defined using either `--task-kill`, `--console` or `--shortcut`. These actions will be mapped to the previously defined controller --input key combinations in the order `--task-kill`, `--console` and finally `--shortcut`\n    - Example with 2 mappings: \n    ```console\n    poetry run controller_companion --input A,B Back,Left --console explorer.exe --shortcut alt+f4\n    ```\n    will result in the following mapping:\n    ```console\n    Controller<A,B> --> Action<name: Run command \"explorer.exe\", target: explorer.exe, type: CONSOLE_COMMAND>\n    Controller<Back,Left> --> Action<name: Shortcut \"alt+f4\", target: alt+f4, type: KEYBOARD_SHORTCUT>\n    ```\n\n    - Run `poetry run controller_companion --help` to see all available arguments\n\n## Build Executable\nWith [poetry](https://python-poetry.org/) installed, run the following command to build the executable using [PyInstaller](https://pyinstaller.org):\n```console \npoetry run build\n```\n\n## Screenshots\n### Main Window\n![demo](demo/app.png)\n### Create a new shortcut \n![demo](demo/add_new_shortcut.png)\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "controller_companion", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "controller_companion.VERSION", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "controller_companion.version", "xref": {"fqname": "importlib.metadata.version", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "controller_companion.controller", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "controller_companion.controller.Controller", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "controller_companion.controller.Controller.name", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "controller_companion.controller.Controller.guid", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "controller_companion.controller.Controller.power_level", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "controller_companion.controller.Controller.instance_id", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "controller_companion.controller.Controller.initialized", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref